<title>SPAIN: Spain's Ercros sees 1997 profit up 35 pct.</title>
<headline>Spain's Ercros sees 1997 profit up 35 pct.</headline>
<dateline>MADRID 1997-06-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Spanish chemical group Ercros on Friday forecasts a 35 percent increase in 1997 profit to one billion pesetas, on turnover set to rise three percent to 39 billion.</p>
<p>Chairman Antonio Zabalza told shareholders Ercros could again become one of Spain's leading industrial companies.</p>
<p>In a statement the company said it demonstraed in 1996 that it can produce profits even during a downturn in the cycle. Last year the firm posted a 33 percent fall in earnings to 737 million pesetas.</p>
<p>-- Madrid newsroom +341 585 2160</p>
